{"meta":{"category_id":"staff_ai_engineer_eea","category_name":"Staff AI Engineer — EEA","macro_family":"ai_engineering_adjacent","priority":"secondary_target","confidence":"high","total_jobs":34,"deep_analysis_count":20,"low_sample_mode":false,"noisy_title_mode":false,"uncertainty_note":"Moderate sample with strong consistency: emphasize repeated architecture, delivery, reliability, and evaluation signals; avoid overfitting around niche frameworks, domains, or formal management because those remain low-frequency in this category."},"category_signature":{"one_sentence_summary":"A top-third CV for this category should present a senior IC or light player-coach who ships production AI platforms and features, proves architecture and reliability outcomes, and translates cross-functional needs into scalable applied AI systems rather than pure research or formal people management.","distinctive_signals":["Architecture/platform scope is the clearest category anchor: platform design appears in 34/34 roles (100%), with most roles spanning both greenfield and optimization work (28/34).","This category is delivery-heavy and senior-IC-led: senior_ic appears in 34/34 roles, with scope split between IC (19/34) and player-coach (15/34), while hiring (3/34, 8.8%) and performance management (1/34, 2.9%) stay rare.","GenAI emphasis is practical rather than research-led: evaluation/quality is stronger (15/34, 44.1%) than RAG (10/34, 29.4%), agents/orchestration (9/34, 26.5%), prompt engineering (8/34, 23.5%), or fine-tuning (4/34, 11.8%)."],"citations":["Platform design 34/34 (100%); greenfield+optimization 28/34.","Seniority: senior_ic 34/34; role scope IC 19/34, player-coach 15/34.","Management signals: hiring 3/34 (8.8%), org building 8/34 (23.5%), performance management 1/34 (2.9%).","AI stack: evaluation_quality 15/34 (44.1%), RAG 10/34 (29.4%), agents_orchestration 9/34 (26.5%), prompt_engineering 8/34 (23.5%), fine_tuning 4/34 (11.8%).","Research-heavy and PhD requirements each 1/34 (2.9%)."]},"headline_pattern":{"recommended_structure":"<Staff|Principal> AI Engineer | Applied AI Platform & Architecture | Production GenAI, Evaluation, Reliability","safe_title_families":["Staff Engineer","Principal Engineer"],"safe_title_variants":["Staff AI Engineer","Principal AI Engineer","Principal AI/ML Engineer","Staff Software Engineer - Applied AI","Staff Software Engineer (Platform - GenAI)"],"avoid_title_variants":["Director of AI Engineering","Head of AI","VP Engineering","AI Research Lead","Engineering Manager"],"evidence_first_rules":["Use a Staff/Principal headline only when the CV already shows senior IC scope; title families cluster around staff_engineer (20/34) and principal_engineer (13/34).","Add an architecture/platform qualifier because platform design is universal in this sample (34/34, 100%).","Add GenAI or applied AI language only if the experience proves production delivery, evaluation, RAG, agents, or guardrails; no single technical keyword exceeds 60%, so keep the headline evidence-backed rather than tool-stuffed.","Do not imply formal people management, hiring ownership, or org leadership in the headline because those signals are limited: hiring 3/34 (8.8%), org building 8/34 (23.5%), performance management 1/34 (2.9%)."],"citations":["Title families: staff_engineer 20/34, principal_engineer 13/34, senior_engineer 1/34.","Platform design 34/34 (100%).","Management signals: hiring 3/34 (8.8%), org building 8/34 (23.5%), performance management 1/34 (2.9%).","No hard skill crosses 60%; top hard skill Python is 11/34 (32.4%)."]},"tagline_profile_angle":{"positioning_angle":["Position as a hands-on architect for production AI systems who combines platform design, delivery ownership, and reliability evidence.","Show light technical leadership through mentoring, design influence, and stakeholder translation without overstating formal management."],"foreground":["Production architecture, system integration, reliability, evaluation quality, and scalable delivery across AI-enabled platforms.","Cross-functional execution and communication: collaboration 29/34 (85.3%), communication 23/34 (67.6%), mentoring 20/34 (58.8%).","Applied GenAI patterns when true: evaluation/quality 15/34 (44.1%), RAG 10/34 (29.4%), agents/orchestration 9/34 (26.5%), prompt engineering 8/34 (23.5%)."],"avoid":["Research-centric positioning, publication language, or PhD-style framing.","Pure people-manager positioning or hiring-led narrative.","Niche stack laundry lists unsupported by outcomes."],"safe_positioning":["Staff/principal-level AI platform engineer who designs and productionizes scalable AI systems.","Senior IC or player-coach who improves reliability, latency, evaluation quality, and adoption of AI capabilities.","Architect-level engineer who bridges product, platform, and ML delivery in distributed environments."],"unsafe_positioning":["Formal org owner, people manager, or hiring lead unless explicitly evidenced.","Deep domain specialist in healthcare, fintech, observability, or consulting unless repeated work history proves it.","Cloud- or tooling-specific specialist claims such as deep Azure, Oracle, Grafana, Prometheus, or OpenTelemetry ownership unless explicitly evidenced."],"citations":["Collaboration 29/34 (85.3%), communication 23/34 (67.6%), mentoring 20/34 (58.8%), leadership 14/34 (41.2%).","Evaluation_quality 15/34 (44.1%), RAG 10/34 (29.4%), agents_orchestration 9/34 (26.5%), prompt_engineering 8/34 (23.5%).","Research-heavy 1/34 (2.9%), PhD required 1/34 (2.9%).","Unsafe claims sample includes formal people-management org ownership, strategic hiring ownership, deep healthcare ownership, deep consulting background, observability tool ownership, and deep oracle cloud specialization."]},"core_competency_themes":[{"section_name":"Architecture And Productionization","themes":[{"theme":"AI platform architecture and system design","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category consistently rewards engineers who can design reusable AI-enabled platforms and services, not just model experiments; platform design appears in 34/34 roles (100%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keyword. Mention 'AI platform', 'architecture', or 'system design' 2-3 times across headline, profile, and experience if true.","citation":"Platform design 34/34 (100%); valued evidence type architecture 20/20 deep-analysis samples."},{"theme":"Greenfield plus optimization delivery","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Top profiles show both building new systems and improving existing ones, which matches the dominant delivery pattern in the sample.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keyword. Mention 'greenfield', 'modernization', 'optimization', or equivalent 1-2 times if true.","citation":"Greenfield split: both 28/34, greenfield-only 1/34, optimization-only 1/34."},{"theme":"Distributed systems and service integration","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"The role sits closer to platform and production engineering than to isolated model work, so distributed systems, APIs, microservices, and integration depth can separate stronger CVs.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keyword cluster. Mention the strongest true terms 1-2 times; use niche infrastructure names once only if true.","citation":"Distributed systems 4/34 (11.8%), microservices 4/34 (11.8%), APIs 3/34 (8.8%); pain points emphasize robust data flows, serving APIs, large-scale maintainability, and low latency."}]},{"section_name":"Reliability Quality And Operations","themes":[{"theme":"Reliability and operational resilience","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Reliability is repeatedly valued in deep analysis and in success metrics, so CV bullets should prove stable production operation rather than only feature shipment.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keyword. Mention 'reliability', 'resilience', 'high availability', or equivalent 2-3 times across profile and quantified bullets if true.","citation":"Valued evidence type reliability 18/20; success metrics include reliability, resilience, and high availability; monitoring appears in 4/34 (11.8%)."},{"theme":"Evaluation and quality measurement for AI systems","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Evaluation is the strongest AI-specific signal in this category and distinguishes production-minded AI engineers from generic GenAI implementers.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keyword. Mention 'evaluation', 'quality', 'benchmarking', or 'offline/online eval' 2-3 times if true.","citation":"Evaluation_quality 15/34 (44.1%); valued evidence type evaluation 15/20 deep-analysis samples."},{"theme":"Performance, latency, and scalability outcomes","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Hiring pain points repeatedly mention low latency, high throughput, and maintainable scale, so outcome metrics here carry more weight than generic model claims.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keyword cluster. Mention latency, throughput, scale, cost, or operational excellence 1-2 times each when evidenced.","citation":"Valued evidence types scale 14/20 and cost 11/20; success metrics include scalability, performance, operational excellence, latency optimization; pain points cite low-latency and high-throughput constraints."}]},{"section_name":"Applied GenAI Delivery","themes":[{"theme":"RAG and retrieval-grounded AI systems","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"RAG is meaningful in this category but not universal, so it should strengthen the CV when real delivery evidence exists rather than dominate the narrative by default.","ats_guidance":"Strong secondary keyword. Mention 'RAG' or 'retrieval' 1-2 times if true; do not force it into every section.","citation":"RAG 10/34 (29.4%); vector_search 6/34 (17.6%)."},{"theme":"Agents and orchestration workflows","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Agentic workflows appear often enough to matter, especially when tied to production controls, reuse, or automation outcomes.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keyword. Mention 'agents', 'orchestration', or 'workflow automation' 1-2 times if true; keep specific frameworks once only.","citation":"Agents_orchestration 9/34 (26.5%); hard skill agentic workflows 3/34 (8.8%)."},{"theme":"Guardrails, prompting, and safe AI behavior","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"These signals support stronger applied AI stories, but they are still weaker than evaluation and platform delivery, so they should not anchor the whole CV unless deeply evidenced.","ats_guidance":"Niche keyword cluster. Mention guardrails, governance, prompt engineering, or routing once each and only if true.","citation":"Prompt_engineering 8/34 (23.5%), guardrails_governance 5/34 (14.7%), model_serving_routing 1/34 (2.9%)."}]},{"section_name":"Technical Leadership Without Formal Management","themes":[{"theme":"Cross-functional collaboration and communication","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This role requires translating architecture and delivery choices across product, platform, and engineering stakeholders; collaboration and communication are the most repeated soft-skill signals.","ats_guidance":"Strongest soft-skill keywords. Mention collaboration and communication 2-3 times across summary and leadership bullets if true.","citation":"Collaboration 29/34 (85.3%), communication 23/34 (67.6%), cross-functional collaboration 8/34 (23.5%)."},{"theme":"Mentoring and technical guidance","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Mentoring is common and supports a player-coach profile, but it should be framed as technical uplift rather than line management.","ats_guidance":"Secondary soft-skill keyword. Mention mentoring or coaching 1-2 times if true, ideally attached to code quality, architecture reviews, or team velocity outcomes.","citation":"Mentoring 20/34 (58.8%), leadership 14/34 (41.2%), role scope player-coach 15/34."},{"theme":"Org influence without people-management inflation","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Some roles include broader org-shaping influence, but the evidence does not support treating formal org ownership as standard for the category.","ats_guidance":"Niche phrasing only. Use 'influenced roadmap', 'aligned teams', or 'raised engineering standards' once if true; avoid manager language unless explicit.","citation":"Org_building 8/34 (23.5%), hiring 3/34 (8.8%), performance_management 1/34 (2.9%)."}]}],"key_achievement_archetypes":[{"rank":1,"archetype":"Built or evolved a production AI platform used by multiple teams or workflows","what_it_proves":"Shows the category's core value: platform architecture plus real delivery, reuse, and adoption at senior IC scope.","pain_points_addressed":["build reusable ml infrastructure that supports training, deployment, and iteration","integrate ai/ml into product or platform stacks","keep systems maintainable, scalable, and low latency at large scale"],"metrics_to_include":["number of teams or products onboarded","throughput, requests, or user volume","deployment frequency or lead time","adoption rate or active users","latency and uptime improvements"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS: state the platform gap, the architecture you designed, the implementation scope you personally led, and quantified adoption/reliability outcomes. Keep the story centered on productionization, not abstract strategy.","citation":"Platform design 34/34 (100%); valued evidence types architecture 20/20, delivery 20/20, reliability 18/20, scale 14/20."},{"rank":2,"archetype":"Improved AI system quality with evaluation, benchmarking, or feedback loops","what_it_proves":"Demonstrates mature applied AI engineering and distinguishes the CV from generic GenAI delivery claims.","pain_points_addressed":["make search, recommendation, or AI outputs more relevant","improve reliability and production quality","reduce regressions while iterating on AI features"],"metrics_to_include":["quality lift, accuracy, precision/recall, or ranking gains","regression rate reduction","human review pass rate","incident reduction","time-to-detect or time-to-fix quality issues"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR with a quality bottleneck as the tension point. Show the evaluation method you introduced, how it changed decisions or release safety, and the measurable quality or reliability gain.","citation":"Evaluation_quality 15/34 (44.1%); valued evidence type evaluation 15/20; success metrics include reliability, performance, and operational excellence."},{"rank":3,"archetype":"Shipped retrieval or agent workflows with safe operational behavior","what_it_proves":"Shows practical GenAI experience in the patterns most relevant to this category without drifting into research framing.","pain_points_addressed":["use llms and agents to automate workflows","ground model outputs with retrieval","control failure modes, cost, and latency in AI services"],"metrics_to_include":["task completion or automation rate","cost per request or inference spend","latency or timeout reduction","fallback rate or error rate","user adoption or productivity gains"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS and explicitly name the workflow boundary, retrieval/agent design, and the controls that made it production-safe. Tie the result to cost, latency, quality, or adoption rather than novelty.","citation":"RAG 10/34 (29.4%), agents_orchestration 9/34 (26.5%), prompt_engineering 8/34 (23.5%), guardrails_governance 5/34 (14.7%), cost evidence 11/20."},{"rank":4,"archetype":"Scaled an AI-enabled service under latency, throughput, or reliability constraints","what_it_proves":"Signals that the candidate can handle the production engineering side of applied AI, which is central to staff/principal hiring in this sample.","pain_points_addressed":["run low-latency, high-throughput systems","move models into production search or recommendation flows","keep systems maintainable and resilient at user scale"],"metrics_to_include":["p95/p99 latency","throughput or QPS","availability/SLO attainment","error budget or incident counts","infrastructure cost at scale"],"story_format_guidance":"Frame the story around an operational constraint. Show the architecture or service changes you drove and end with hard reliability, latency, or scale numbers.","citation":"Success metrics include scalability, performance, resilience, reliability, high availability, and latency optimization; valued evidence types reliability 18/20, scale 14/20, cost 11/20."},{"rank":5,"archetype":"Raised team delivery standards through technical leadership and mentoring","what_it_proves":"Supports a player-coach profile without overclaiming formal management and aligns with the category's strong collaboration and mentoring evidence.","pain_points_addressed":["align cross-functional teams on architecture choices","improve execution quality across platform and product work","help teams adopt reusable AI patterns safely"],"metrics_to_include":["number of engineers mentored","review or delivery cycle improvements","reduction in defects or rework","adoption of standards, templates, or playbooks","cross-team delivery cadence"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR with a delivery or quality coordination problem. Emphasize architecture reviews, standards, or mentoring actions and quantify the team-level effect without slipping into manager language.","citation":"Collaboration 29/34 (85.3%), communication 23/34 (67.6%), mentoring 20/34 (58.8%), player-coach scope 15/34, org_building 8/34 (23.5%)."}],"role_weighting_guidance":{"highest_weight_roles":["Staff/principal IC roles with platform, architecture, or applied AI delivery scope.","Technical lead or architect roles where the candidate designed production systems and influenced multiple teams.","Senior engineering roles with clear reliability, scale, API, distributed-systems, or MLOps-style outcomes that map into AI platform work."],"expand_in_work_history":["Roles with direct evidence of platform design, reusable infrastructure, production AI delivery, evaluation, reliability, or cross-team architecture influence.","Work that shows both greenfield building and optimization of existing systems.","Bullets with measurable outcomes in latency, uptime, quality, scalability, or adoption."],"compress_in_work_history":["Older roles that are primarily feature delivery without architecture scope.","Work centered on narrow tools or domains that do not map to platform, AI delivery, or production reliability.","People-management details unless they are explicit and material, because formal management is not the dominant pattern in this category."],"how_to_frame_non_ai_experience":["Translate non-AI platform work into transferable signals: distributed systems, APIs, microservices, cloud delivery, CI/CD, observability, reliability, and scale.","If the candidate has strong architecture experience outside AI, tie it forward to productionizing AI systems rather than pretending deep model specialization.","Use prior search, data, adtech, or backend scale work to prove relevance, ranking, routing, throughput, or serving depth when true."],"citations":["Title families: staff_engineer 20/34, principal_engineer 13/34.","Platform design 34/34 (100%); greenfield+optimization 28/34.","Valued evidence types architecture 20/20, delivery 20/20, reliability 18/20, scale 14/20.","Management signals remain limited: hiring 3/34 (8.8%), performance management 1/34 (2.9%)."]},"language_and_tone":{"recommended_tone":"player_coach","formality":"high","preferred_vocabulary":["platform architecture","production AI systems","applied AI","reliability","evaluation","scalability","low latency","cross-functional delivery","technical leadership","mentoring","distributed systems","system integration"],"avoid_vocabulary":["visionary","thought leader","AI evangelist","research pioneer","best-in-class","owned hiring","built the entire org","end-to-end compliance owner","deep domain expert"],"citations":["Role scope: IC 19/34, player-coach 15/34; senior_ic 34/34.","Soft skills: collaboration 29/34 (85.3%), communication 23/34 (67.6%), mentoring 20/34 (58.8%).","Architecture/platform scope 34/34 (100%); management signals remain modest."]},"unsafe_or_weak_framing":{"avoid_claims":["Formal people-management org ownership unless explicitly evidenced; unsafe claim examples include formal people-management org ownership and direct people management or hiring ownership.","Strategic hiring ownership unless explicitly evidenced; hiring appears in only 3/34 roles (8.8%).","Deep healthcare, fintech, observability, consulting, or Oracle-specialist positioning unless repeated work history proves it.","Hands-on ownership of Grafana, Prometheus, Loki, Tempo, or OpenTelemetry in production unless the CV clearly shows it.","Primary ownership of front-end or unrelated stacks such as Ruby on Rails and React unless supported by actual experience.","End-to-end compliance, HIPAA, patient-safety, or responsible-AI program ownership unless explicitly stated."],"buzzword_patterns":["Do not stack 'LLMs, agents, RAG, guardrails, vector DBs, orchestration' without outcome evidence.","Do not use framework-heavy summaries when frameworks are individually sparse in the sample.","Do not present GenAI features as the whole job; keep architecture, delivery, reliability, and evaluation in front."],"title_inflation_risks":["Avoid upgrading senior engineer experience into staff/principal unless multi-team architecture and delivery scope is visible.","Avoid manager or director titles when the evidence supports senior IC or light player-coach positioning.","Avoid 'AI Research Lead' framing because research-heavy demand is only 1/34 (2.9%)."],"research_framing_risks":["Keep publications, research, and PhD language out of positive positioning unless directly required by the target role.","Do not imply research ownership, model invention, or academic specialization from applied platform work."],"domain_or_region_risks":["Do not claim native-language requirements; none are evidenced in the deep-analysis summary.","Do not overstate remote-only preference even though remote-first appears often; present distributed collaboration as a working style, not a core identity.","Do not overfit the CV to one vertical because domain distribution is mixed and shallow: fintech 3/34, healthcare 3/34, consulting 2/34, enterprise SaaS 2/34."],"citations":["Unsafe claims sample includes formal people-management org ownership, strategic hiring ownership, deep healthcare ownership, observability ownership at scale, deep Oracle specialization, deep consulting background, and unsupported stack ownership.","Hiring 3/34 (8.8%), performance management 1/34 (2.9%), org_building 8/34 (23.5%).","Research-heavy 1/34 (2.9%), requires_phd 1/34 (2.9%).","Native language requirements: none. Domain distribution: fintech 3/34, healthcare 3/34, consulting 2/34, enterprise_saas 2/34."]},"evidence_ledger":[{"recommendation":"Anchor the CV around production AI platform architecture and delivery rather than generic GenAI enthusiasm.","support":["Platform design 34/34 (100%).","Valued evidence types architecture 20/20 and delivery 20/20.","Title families concentrate in staff_engineer 20/34 and principal_engineer 13/34."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Use a senior IC or light player-coach narrative, not a formal management narrative.","support":["Seniority distribution: senior_ic 34/34.","Role scope: IC 19/34, player-coach 15/34.","Hiring 3/34 (8.8%), performance management 1/34 (2.9%), org_building 8/34 (23.5%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Prioritize quantified reliability, evaluation, scale, latency, and cost outcomes in bullet writing.","support":["Valued evidence types: reliability 18/20, evaluation 15/20, scale 14/20, cost 11/20.","Success metrics include scalability, performance, resilience, reliability, operational excellence, and latency optimization.","Pain points repeatedly emphasize maintainability, low latency, throughput, and production serving."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Treat RAG and agents as differentiators, not universal anchors, unless the candidate truly has them.","support":["RAG 10/34 (29.4%), agents_orchestration 9/34 (26.5%), prompt_engineering 8/34 (23.5%).","No hard skill crosses 60%; Python is highest at 11/34 (32.4%) in hard_skills_top and 12/34 (35.3%) in language requirements."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Repeat a small set of true keywords instead of listing many niche tools.","support":["ATS strategy should center on strongest repeated concepts because the long-tail frameworks are sparse: PyTorch 6/34 (17.6%), LangChain 4/34 (11.8%), LangGraph 1/34 (2.9%), LlamaIndex 1/34 (2.9%).","No single technical keyword is universal in this category."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Keep research, publication, and PhD framing inside risk controls only.","support":["Research-heavy 1/34 (2.9%).","Requires PhD 1/34 (2.9%)."],"confidence":"high"} 	,{"recommendation":"State distributed collaboration and mentoring when true, but avoid overclaiming org ownership or regional specialization.","support":["Collaboration 29/34 (85.3%), communication 23/34 (67.6%), mentoring 20/34 (58.8%).","Remote-first 11/34, distributed 5/34, hybrid 3/34.","Native language requirements are absent; domain and region-specific signals are weak."],"confidence":"medium"} 	,{"recommendation":"Use keyword repetition selectively: strongest 4-6 keywords 2-3 mentions each if true; secondary 4-6 keywords 1-2 mentions each if true; niche keywords once only and only if true.","support":["Strong repeated category concepts are architecture/platform, reliability, evaluation, collaboration, communication, mentoring, and production AI delivery.","The long-tail stack evidence is fragmented, so over-repetition of niche tools would overfit the CV."],"confidence":"high"}] }
